A telesync is a video copy of the movie which was shot in a Movie theater, often with a professional camera on a tripod in the projection booth, with a direct connection to the sound source (often FM audio provided for the hearing-impaired, or from a drive-in theater). A telesync is a special type of cam that has the potential of better-quality audio and video.
